  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>GE Café in LA — the design-first refrigerator for interior-designer kitchens</h2>
      <p>
        GE Café has carved out a distinct position in the LA premium refrigerator market: the design-first choice
        for kitchens where the aesthetic matters as much as the function. Matte Black and Matte White finishes
        reference contemporary design trends (they coordinate with Matte-finish cabinetry, Matte tile, and the
        broader design-forward kitchen movement from the late 2010s onward), and the customizable handle hardware
        — Brushed Stainless, Brushed Copper, Brushed Bronze, Brushed Black — lets a client coordinate the fridge
        trim to whatever cabinet hardware they choose. That's a genuine differentiator no other luxury refrigerator
        brand offers.
      </p>
      <p>
        The LA Café service territory concentrates in interior-designer-partnered kitchens — Hollywood Hills
        contemporary renovations, Beverly Hills and Westside design-forward updates, and Silver Lake / Venice /
        Echo Park kitchens where the design-first aesthetic is part of the architectural vocabulary. The Café
        clientele is noticeably different from the Profile clientele: Profile homes prioritize feature richness;
        Café homes prioritize aesthetic coherence with the kitchen's broader design story. For service, what that
        means is we handle handle swaps as a regular service category (the kind of work that doesn't exist on
        other brands) and we pay close attention to Matte finish preservation during any exterior work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>GE Café refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our GE Café coverage. Café shares most of its underlying refrigeration platform with GE
        Profile, so the core failure patterns are similar — but Café adds handle-hardware and Matte-finish-specific
        service items that Profile doesn't have.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Handle-swap service — the Café-exclusive service category</h3>
        <p>
          Routine service request. Client wants to change handle finish (common: Brushed Stainless → Brushed Bronze
          when the kitchen cabinet hardware is updated). Our guys bring the handle kit (sourced via GE Café parts
          channel, finish-specific), remove existing handles carefully to preserve Matte finish, install new handles
          to torque spec. 45–60 minute visit. Handle kit parts $150–$380 depending on finish; labor $120–$180. No
          other luxury refrigerator brand in LA offers this service because the hardware isn't user-replaceable
          on competitor products.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Slow ice production — LA hard-water pattern</h3>
        <p>
          Same pattern as all GE Appliances French Door models in LA hard-water neighborhoods. Fill valve scales,
          flow drops, ice-mold fills partially. Descale + valve $280–$440. Module swap $420–$620 when warranted.
          Verify water filter age first (homeowner-installable, no service call needed for routine filter swap).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Matte finish damage requiring factory panel replacement</h3>
        <p>
          Scratches, dents, or cleaning-product damage to Matte Black or Matte White exteriors — replacement
          through GE Appliances Café parts channel with factory-matched Matte finish. Lead times 2–4 weeks.
          Protect Matte finishes with gentle cleaning products only; our techs educate homeowners during service
          when we see finish care issues.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>SmartHQ / voice integration setup and maintenance</h3>
        <p>
          Wi-Fi drops, Alexa/Google skill authorization expiring, SmartHQ app versioning mismatches. Our
          diagnostic: router-side first, firmware second, Wi-Fi module last. Most cases resolve at firmware or
          re-authorization level. Firmware update $120–$180; Wi-Fi module replacement $220–$360.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Water dispenser fill valve service</h3>
        <p>
          No flow at dispenser, low pressure, or slow dispense. Test inlet pressure, inspect filter, verify fill
          valve solenoid. Replacement $220–$340 for fill valve; $180–$280 for dispenser solenoid.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor and refrigeration-cycle reliability — running solid</h3>
        <p>
          Café's underlying refrigeration platform is shared with GE Profile and runs the GE Appliances variable-
          speed compressor architecture. Field data 2017–2025 shows similar reliability patterns to Profile —
          10–14 year compressor life typical, capacitor faults emerging at the 10-year mark before compressor
          failure, sealed-system faults uncommon. Post-warranty compressor replacement $900–$1,500 when needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>GE Café US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        GE Café refrigeration centers on French Door, Counter-Depth, and 4-Door configurations with Matte finish
        options and customizable hardware. Keurig-integrated variant lives on a dedicated page.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Counter-Depth French Door (CWE prefix)</h3>
          <p>36-inch and 33-inch widths, counter-depth profile. French Door upper, freezer drawer lower. Matte
          Black, Matte White, or Platinum Glass finish. Customizable handles. SmartHQ Wi-Fi. The most-common LA
          Café install.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Full-Depth French Door (CFE prefix)</h3>
          <p>Deeper body depth with larger internal capacity. Same aesthetic options as Counter-Depth. Good value
          for larger households or entertaining kitchens where counter-depth isn't critical.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>4-Door French Door</h3>
          <p>French Door upper plus twin-drawer lower (fridge-drawer + freezer-drawer). More compartment
          flexibility. Popular in larger Café installs in Hollywood Hills and Beverly Hills design-forward
          kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Matte Black finish</h3>
          <p>Signature Café finish. Factory-applied Matte Black over stainless substrate. Coordinates with
          contemporary Matte-finish cabinetry. Requires specific cleaning products (not standard stainless
          polish). Factory-matched replacement panels via Café parts channel.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Matte White finish</h3>
          <p>The lighter Matte option. Same factory-applied process as Matte Black. Works in kitchens with lighter
          cabinetry, farmhouse-contemporary design language, or spaces where the fridge is meant to recede rather
          than anchor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Customizable handle hardware (Café-exclusive)</h3>
          <p>Four factory-available finishes: Brushed Stainless (standard), Brushed Copper, Brushed Bronze, Brushed
          Black. User-orderable kits, tech-installable. Swap service $120–$180 labor, kit $150–$380 parts. Feature
          no competitor offers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
