        <b>Samsung Bespoke</b> — Samsung's design-focused line with interchangeable color panels. Direct visual
        competitor to Café on modularity and aesthetic customization. See
        <a href="/brands/samsung-refrigerator-repair/">Samsung refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>LG InstaView</b> — Door-in-Door innovation, instant-view glass panel. Design-forward but different
        direction than Café's Matte finish. See <a href="/brands/lg-refrigerator-repair/">LG refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Café</b> — Matte finishes plus customizable handle hardware, US-manufactured, Haier-backed, strong
        SmartHQ Wi-Fi ecosystem. Best pick when the household wants design customization integrated into a US-made
        product with straightforward service infrastructure. Sibling tiers:
        <a href="/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/">GE Profile</a> (feature-focused mid-premium),
        <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">GE Monogram</a> (ultra-luxury built-in), and
        <a href="/brands/ge-refrigerator-repair/">GE</a> (base tier). For the unique Keurig-integrated Café variant,
        see <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-keurig-refrigerator-repair/">GE Café Keurig refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        None is objectively better — they're positioned differently within design-forward premium. Café's handle
        customization is the genuinely unique feature in the LA market.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

